Name: Memory Fragment (inventory)
Description: The shattered remnants of an expired traveller<>. It whispers, an unknowable name deep within its fibres. The memory will manifest as an inventory expansion<> to aid you on your travels. Absorb<> this memory with FE_ALT1<><>.

Name: Wormskin Folio: 1
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'The worm lord towers above the dusty earth; its flesh becomes the sky.
Our pathetic shells cannot follow, cannot reach its height, cannot reach its depths.
We offer ourselves to the ground.
We beg our sacrifice accepted.'

Name: Wormskin Folio: 2
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'The dust was choking. 
Our eyes reddened and watered. 
But the truth was inescapable.
The veins of the Atlas had surfaced.'

Name: Wormskin Folio: 3
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'Now with every storm we beg to be chosen;
Arms to the sky, faces to the dirt, calling out with all we have!
When heavy raindrops hit the earth, the veins of Atlas answer.
The rapture of our consumption is beyond words.'

Name: Wormskin Folio: 4
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'We tumble as it swallows, but grip the slick walls as best we can - 
Oh! - to reach the gizzard still awake. 
Breathe it deeply! How our lungs gurgle!
The slime clogs our noses and stings our eyes, 
though in this warm darkness, we are already blind.'

Name: Wormskin Folio: 5
Description:
Ancient words are carved into this <STELLAR>living document<>. They read:

'Curse the agony of regurgitation, 
Curse this this feeble flesh that still confines me!
My brethren were reborn, rising from the blessed dust as fresh tendrils. 
Glistening capillaries to the great veins, slithering away into the sand.
I will be patient. Until the next storm.'

Name: Pirate Map Fragment 1 of 3
Description:
Partial coordinate data, acquired from a troubled <STELLAR>freighter captain<>. The chart is signed with a snippet of pirate manifesto:

"We Blight this new galaxy, as we did the last, as we will the next!"

The data is of value to pirate faction <SPECIAL>The Blight<>, who attempted to retrieve it by violent means.

Name: Pirate Map Fragment 2 of 3
Description:
Partial coordinate data, acquired from a <STELLAR>freighter<> shot down by pirate faction <SPECIAL>The Blight<>. The chart is signed with a snippet of pirate manifesto:

"The galactic tunnels belong to the Blight!"

The navigational information is corrupted, but appears to be linked to the data acquired from the <STELLAR>freighter captain<>.

Name: Pirate Map Fragment 3 of 3
Description:
Partial coordinate data, acquired from a <STELLAR>starship<> crashed on an ocean bed. The chart is signed with a snippet of pirate manifesto:

"Annihilate every Traveller! All galaxies will fall to Blight!"

The navigational information is unreadable in its current state, but appears to be linked to the data acquired from the <STELLAR>freighter captain<>.

Name: Rendezvous Beacon
Description: An unmarked navigation beacon<>, acquired from the wreck of a downed starship. Use Activate Beacon (FE_ALT1<>) to deploy the beacon and retrace the final steps of the crashed ship.

Name: Ticket to Freedom
Description: "Glorious survivor! The promised star<> will be yours!" A Secure system pass<> bearing the mark of the 'Voice of Freedom'<>. Select the pass and use Accept Invitation (FE_ALT1<>) to pin the location in your navigation systems.

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT I
Description:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"The leviathan was like nothing I've ever seen.
So vast as to blot out the sun.
I wanted it. I deserve to have it! It will be mine.
But it resisted, would not come quietly.
It wailed and it wailed as the infra-knife carved into its meat.
It almost took me down with it. Perhaps it has. Perhaps..."

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT II
Description:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"The same nightmare chases me: a wail fills my cockpit, the dashboard controls gummed with blood.
I have given up sleep. I pulse past blurred stars.
And then there it was: majestic, drifting in the ocean of space.
Something inside me burns for it. I must have it.
Its great fin flexed toward my ship, and my hull was gone..."

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT III
Description:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"Today should have been the day. Their hour was at hand.
It must be mine. They are like nothing I've ever seen.
Everything was prepared. But it moved faster than I thought possible. As though it knew where I would fly, before I knew it myself.
A great tentacle hugged my ship, my cockpit - pressing my suit down to the bone. This suit will be my grave."

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT IV
Description:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"The chase is over, and I have lost.
The giants will endure, and I will end.
As I plummeted from the sky, I saw another ship falling alongside mine. Then another, and another.
I may have imagined it. The misfiring of a dying mind...
Those creatures were so beautiful. But it is all ended now.
They will haunt my thoughts no longer."

Name: MEMORY IMPRINT V
Description:
A memory is <STELLAR>burned<> into this strange material, an echo of another lifetime...

"I came face-to-face with a creature more beautiful and bizarre than anything I have ever seen.
Despite no discernible eyes, I do not believe it is blind.
It was huge, glorious, serene. But then - with a flick of its tentacles, it was gone.
I have thought of nothing else since. I can only think of the whale. whale. whale. <SPECIAL>wail<>."

Name: Lost Bathysphere
Description:
A haunted <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>. Even once removed, the wearer will forever hear the whispering call of the deep ocean...
Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Shroud of Freedom
Description:
A flowing silken shroud, bestowed upon those who would sing with <SPECIAL>Voice of Freedom<>.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit with this exclusive <STELLAR>Appearance Override<> at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Horizon Vector Nx
Description: An exclusive Starship<>. This compact fighter craft boasts superior manoeuvrability, giving it an edge in space combat. Claim<> this ship to add it to your collection, or Exchange<> it with your current ship. While on a planet, summon ships from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

Name: Infinite Neon Mark Xxii
Description: An exclusive Multi-Tool<>. This brightly-coloured rifle offers the user cutting-edge defensive capabilities in ground combat situations. Take<> this Multi-Tool to add it to your collection, or Exchange<> it with your current Multi-Tool. Swap between active Multi-Tools from the Utilities section of the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

Name: Streamlined Jetpack Unit
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

A streamlined and lightweight backpack unit, featuring an elegant single-thruster design. This exclusive exosuit augmentation commemorates completion of the inaugural <STELLAR>Expedition<>, 'Pioneers'.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Golden First Spawn Battle Mask
Description:
An aggressive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>, modeled on the war helmets of the ancient Gek. This special edition is cast in a durable and precious alloy.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Golden Vector
Description: An exclusive golden edition of the iconic Alpha Vector Starship<>, commemorating completion of the inaugural Expedition<>, 'Pioneers'. This highly-manoeuvrable spacecraft is constructed from a durable and precious alloy, and coated in a tough layer of fibrous insulation to endure many lifetimes' worth of rigorous space exploration. Claim<> this ship to add it to your collection, or Exchange<> it with your current ship. While on a planet, summon ships from the Quick Menu (QUICK_MENU<>).

Name: Title: 'pioneer'
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Explorer Title<>, commemorating completion of the inaugural <STELLAR>Expedition<>, 'Pioneers'.

Apply this title to your banner at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Pioneers Expedition Banner
Description:
Equip this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<> in commemoration of the inaugural <STELLAR>Expedition<>, 'Pioneers'.
Apply this banner to your profile at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Atlas Firework Pack
Description: A three-variety pack of luxury fireworks. These stunning pyrotechnics render the likeness of an Atlas Interface, in bursts of indium<>, gold<> and cadmium<>. Ignite to create glittering displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

Name: Flesh Launcher Pack
Description: A pack of luxury fireworks. These organic pyrotechnics rocket into the sky and explode in a splatter of slime, mucus, and wormlets. Ignite to create disgusting displays in the sky. Place launch tube via the Build Menu<> (BUILD_MENU<>). Warning<>: Aim away from living creatures. Not recommended for indoor use.

Name: Ssv Normandy Sr1
Description:
The <TECHNOLOGY>SSV Normandy SR1<> is a one-of-a-kind 'deep scout' frigate. This legendary ship represents peace and cooperation between races, and commemorates completion of the 'Beachhead' <STELLAR>Expedition<>.

Recruiting this frigate will add it to your fleet. Manage your frigate fleet from a <TECHNOLOGY>Fleet Command Room<> aboard your freighter, and consult your <TECHNOLOGY>Navigator<> to deploy frigates on lucrative expeditions.

Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Specially conditioned oil is added to the jetpack's exhaust jets, creating a stream of pearlescent bubbles as it operates.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Ghastly Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Attaches an active bio-chamber to the Jetpack's exhaust nozzles. During flight, the thrusters warm and expel the slimy juice contained within.
<STELLAR>Note<>: Contains living worms. Ejected worms may infest local ecosystems.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Whispering Companion Egg
Description:
A living, fertile egg, <TRADEABLE>ready to hatch!<>

A shadow writhes beneath the egg's protective membrane.

Scans indicate the being within has the genetic potential to be <FUEL>nightmarish<> and <FUEL>soul-consuming<>.

Name: Sandworm Egg
Description:
A living, fertile egg, <TRADEABLE>ready to hatch!<>

Curled within the shell is a hungry wormlet, its coils rippling restlessly.

Scans indicate the being within has the genetic potential to be <FUEL>cursed<> and <FUEL>insatiable<>.

Name: Feasting Casque
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

Redistribute your facial organs and alarm other explorers by assuming the appearance of a sandworm cultist. This bio-silicone helmet is sealed against all known planetary hazards, but may feel slightly clammy to the wearer.

Ritualistically transform the head of your <STELLAR>Vy'keen<> appearance at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Reality Glitch Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

The jetpack exhaust is fitted with a high-concentrate pugneum dispenser. When the jets are activated, the resulting reaction carves miniature distortions in reality, and creates an interesting visual effect.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Exotic Armour
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Companion Appearance Enhancement<>. Ideal for fierce-tempered companions, this stylish plate armour protects vital organs against laser and projectile fire. Ultra-soft breathable padding reduces the likelihood of companions wriggling out of the accessory.

Earn the trust of wild animals to adopt companions. Interact with companions to customise their appearance.

Name: Exotic Wingpack
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

An elegant wing-assisted jetpack, inspired by the design philosophy of exotic starships. This exclusive exosuit augmentation commemorates completion of the 'Exobiology' <STELLAR>Expedition<>.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Description:

Description:
A metal 'egg' capsule, <TRADEABLE>ready to hatch!<>

The shell crackles with an electronic energy.

Scans indicate the being within is programmed to be <SPECIAL>tireless<> and <SPECIAL>watchful<>.

Name: Sputtering Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

A ramshackle ship exhaust nozzle, hand-assembled in an emergency by an outlaw. Has an occasional propensity to explode, but with no adverse effect on flight handling.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Title: 'hunter of the Blight'
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Explorer Title<>, commemorating completion of the <STELLAR>Blighted<> expedition, the glorious retrieval of ill-gotten lucre, and the discovery of a pirate secret.

Apply this title to your banner at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Description:
Equip this exclusive <STELLAR>Personal Flair<> in commemoration of the 'Blighted' <STELLAR>Expedition<>, the glorious retrieval of ill-gotten lucre, and the discovery of a pirate secret.

Name: Outlaw Cape
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Exosuit Appearance Override<>.

A battle-worn cape, stolen from notorious pirate faction <SPECIAL>The Blight<>. Woven from chemically-dipped nano-fibres, the fabric is completely impervious to the heat produced by jetpack exhaust.

Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an <TECHNOLOGY>Appearance Modifier<>.

Name: Temporal Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

A cosmic resonance chamber interacts with starship exhaust, modifying propulsion energy to leave a streak of temporal disturbances.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Whalestalker Cloak
Description:

Install to an <TECHNOLOGY>Inventory Slot<> to decorate your ship's interior.

Name: Chromatic Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Precisely calibrated multi-chromatic injectors alter the Pulse Engine's output, turning the exhaust trail into a vibrant display of colour.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Stealth Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Baryon suppressors alter the Pulse Engine's output, giving a distinct black tint to its signature trail.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Cadmium Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Cadmium injection nozzles add a bold red flair to the Pulse Engine's output.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Emeril Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Emeril injection nozzles add a rich green flair to the Pulse Engine's output.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Golden Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

Gold injection nozzles add a dazzling gold flair to the Pulse Engine's output.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Sputtering Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

A ramshackle ship exhaust nozzle, hand-assembled in an emergency by an outlaw. Has an occasional propensity to explode, but with no adverse effect on flight handling.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Temporal Starship Trail
Description:
An exclusive <STELLAR>Starship Exhaust Modifier<>.

A cosmic resonance chamber interacts with starship exhaust, modifying propulsion energy to leave a streak of temporal disturbances.

Install this <TECHNOLOGY>technology<> in your starship inventory to change the appearance of the engine exhaust trails.

Name: Hardframe Left Arm
Description:
A collection of salvaged components from a Sentinel Hardframe, reconditioned to fit the <TECHNOLOGY>Minotaur<> Heavy Exocraft Hybrid.

When installed alongside a <TECHNOLOGY>Minotaur Laser<>, it transforms the mining laser into a <STELLAR>powerful combat upgrade<> with the ability to deal heavy damaged to <TECHNOLOGY>stunned<> entities.

Name: Hardframe Right Arm
Description: A collection of salvaged components from a Sentinel Hardframe, reconditioned to fit the Minotaur<> Heavy Exocraft Hybrid. This limb override also functions as its own dedicated combat system<>. It deploys high-velocity stun projectiles<> and serves as an excellent support weapon to the Minotaur's primary cannon. Use CYCLEWEAPON<> to cycle available weapon modes.

Name: Hardframe Legs
Description:
A collection of salvaged components from a Sentinel Hardframe, reconditioned to fit the <TECHNOLOGY>Minotaur<> Heavy Exocraft Hybrid.

Installation will significantly improve the Minotaur's <TECHNOLOGY>engine and mobility<> systems.

Name: Memory Resonator
Description: A highly familar, entirely novel, piece of technology, designed by Specialist Polo as part of their loop research<> efforts. It synchronises its vibrations with the underlying song of the universe, allowing it to reveal memory hotspots<> within the loop. Begin the resonance alignment<> process with FE_ALT1<>.

Name: Ticket to Freedom
Description: "Glorious survivor! The promised star<> will be yours!" A Secure system pass<> bearing the mark of the 'Voice of Freedom'<>. Select the pass and use Accept Invitation (FE_ALT1<>) to pin the location in your navigation systems.

Name: Rendezvous Beacon
Description: An unmarked navigation beacon<>, acquired from the wreck of a downed starship. Use Activate Beacon (FE_ALT1<>) to deploy the beacon and retrace the final steps of the crashed ship.

Name: Foundation
Description: The base unit for all construction projects, providing a solid foundation for any structure. Can be anchored to all types of terrain.

Name: Straight Corridor
Description: A standard, straight corridor module for connecting rooms.

Name: L-shaped Corridor
Description: A sturdy, corridor module for connecting rooms, with an L-shaped bend.

Name: T-shaped Corridor
Description: A corridor module with a branching, t-shaped form, for joining multiple rooms.

Name: X-shaped Corridor
Description: An x-shaped corridor unit for connecting four rooms in a cruciform arrangement.

Name: Cylindrical Room
Description: The core module for base construction, providing a generous central space on which to expand.

Name: Tower Module
Description: A tall, stackable tower module, with rigid, reinforced sides and additional weatherproofing to counter exposure to the elements.

Name: Cuboid Room
Description: A small, cuboid construction module that can be stacked or linked to form larger structures.

Name: Bio-dome
Description: An attractive domed room which is perfect for cultivating a wide range of botanical matter.

Name: Curved Cuboid Roof
Description: A curved, glass-fronted roof module that can be stacked or linked to form larger structures.

Name: Curved Cuboid Wall
Description: A curved, cuboid wall module that can be stacked or linked to form larger structures.

Name: Glass Cuboid Room
Description: A cuboid room module which is created almost entirely out of glass. Excellent for observing areas of natural beauty.

Name: Cuboid Room Frame
Description: Lightweight cuboid support structures which can be stacked or linked to form large industrial structures.

Name: Cuboid Inner Door
Description: An inner door module used to divide cuboid rooms.

Name: Cuboid Inner Wall
Description: An inner wall module used to divide cuboid rooms.

Name: Cuboid Roof Cap
Description: A cuboid roof cap used to decorate and reinforce the rooftops of cuboid structures.

Name: Interior Stairs
Description: A set of stairs to improve access inside cuboid structures.

Name: Holo-door
Description: An elegant holographic door which allows quick access to any structure while regulating the temperature and toxicity of the interior.

Name: Viewing Sphere
Description: A self-contained spherical viewing platform which affords the user stunning views of the surrounding environment.

Name: Cylindrical Room Frame
Description: A lightweight, industrial alternative to the standard Cylindrical Room.

Name: Curved Corridor
Description: A sturdy, large corridor module for connecting rooms, with a curved bend.

Name: Square Room
Description: A square alternative to the core module for base construction, providing a generous central space on which to expand.

Name: Square Room
Description: A square alternative to the core module for base construction, providing a generous central space on which to expand.

Name: Landing Pad
Description: A stable, reinforced landing pad for starships.

Name: Save Point
Description: A buildable save point for managing your progress.

Name: Muster Point
Description: A buildable device that can summon your starship to it from any location.

Name: Nomad Geobay
Description: An underground secure parking facility for the Nomad light Exocraft.

Name: Roamer Geobay
Description: An underground secure parking facility for the Roamer medium Exocraft.

Name: Colossus Geobay
Description: An underground secure parking facility for the Colossus large Exocraft.

Name: Pilgrim Geobay
Description: An underground secure parking facility for the Pilgrim light Exocraft.

Name: Infrastructure Ladder
Description: A ladder used in conjunction with Structural Platforms to allow the user to reach great heights with ease.

Name: Linking Post
Description: Basic structural item used in conjunction with wall modules to create 90 degree corners.

Name: Roof Platform
Description: Basic structural item used in conjunction with wall modules to create platforms able to support considerable weight.
